TO ordinal numbers

The patterns used to form ordinal numbers are *parūs* (e.g. *šalultu*) and *paris* {*šalšu*), of which the first one was used for numbers referring to time division. In addition, Akkaddian uses also the afformatives -*ī* (*šamanū*) and -*ay* (*šalšay*). The last portion of the article contains comments to the section on the numerals in Delitzisch 1889 *Grammatik*.
